content: I am so pleased to find this app! Now I can just scan the music sheets to listen to them and start practicing right away! Lovely!:)

Love the app so far. I am not a professional musician, so all I actually use the app for is to hear the tune of a song I need to learn (I play the recorder). I love the fact that you can choose the instrument that plays the song. I would like it if you could play only the notes for one voice at a time, instead of the alto and soprano together. But for my current needs, I love it!
Not bad. I think it is worth the money. However, it does not recognise things like triplets or repeats. Not even from original sheet music.
It's hard to get a good enough picture, but it does play what I can get half descent. I want to find out what some hymns were supposed to sound like, those seems like a way to do that.

I've been looking for an app like this for ages! As a beginner I don't know what some of the songs I ay should sound like. This app scans the music I own and plays it how it should sound! Thank you! The only bad thing is it can take a few pictures in good light before all the notes are recognised.
The best
Best app...
A veces no reconoce las corcheas ni los silencios, podrían mejorar el apartado de edición. Y estaría bueno agragar la opción de metrónomo.

Mixed results the recognition quality is fairly basic, even with perfect input (high resolution images or PDFs in high quality). Notes are often omitted and rhythm is frequently off. Would be amazing to add manual edit feature to help perfect the basic recognition the app does. Can't wait for future versions. Keep up the good work!
Does not read correctly
Very very useful app for learning piano - let's you hear how the music on the pages is meant to sound.
Did not let me play an individual voice part

Help: I snapped a very simple single instrument single note at time Beginner lesson.Followed the guidlines for taking photobwith zero margin. All except one note is greyed out. What I tried multiple times with different sheets but only one or two notes in a page is recognized. All other notes looks fine but greyed out and does no carry over to midi file. Pl help with suggestion. Update: With proper picture the notes are recognized good. This app is useful for Beginners with self learning. Changing to 4 Stars.
replyContent: As mentioned in my email, the photo was very stretched/distorted; looked like a bad photocopy of another sheet. That is the reason why it didn't get recognized. I have fixed it back to common proportions and sent you that; in that picture, everything got read correctly.

content: Ok it cant read triplets it just slows down the tempo and cant read percussion musuc very well and it liks to skip tacets sometimes its good though
Maganda na magaling pa. May isang hiling lang ako, Sana hindi masyadong masilan sa camera. Dahil ang ginagamit ay vivo. Salamat.
worked out the box. easy to use

I like the app but there NEEDS to be a way to insert notes or notations that weren't recognized. I scaned a song and it was barely recognizable because of notes or key signatures that weren't played correctly. Please, please fix this. I really want to use this app, but I kind of can't unless I can fix the music. Please fix.
Didnt really work.
Perfect for choosing a new piece to play when not sure 'how it goes'
It doesnt read hand written notations.
I'm so impressed with this app I already have 50 sheet music songs in my list right now it also plays the music to in case you forgot how to play it
While it does read music well, I've had a very hard time getting it to catch all the notes, it often skips some, even if I have a high quality picture

Excellent product. It would be nice to have the option to reduce the effect level or sustain of the selected instrument sound. Maybe an option to add a missing note/ figure, and comments if required, that would be awesome!☺

For someone who hasn't learned to read music, this app has come in really handy! It helps me prep for worship service, and to learn new songs I am not familiar with. This app is a true blessing and I am SO thankful that it exhists!!!

Pretty awesome if you line up the picture and have a single light source with no shadows or glare on the page. It's cool you can play the single voice or multiple. I like the variety of instruments and how well it recognizes a bar and a rest. One thing I was hoping for is recognizing song structure because I'm stumped on this piece with these double-thin bars, repeat bars, and then the double-thin-thick and the end. But I see that is a planned feature, looking forward to it. Thank you!

I am impressed that the app can read notes from an image, but it did not quite do what I needed. I cannot personally read sheet music and I will need the option to selectively mute or delete notes so that I can practice 4-part vocal harmony pieces without hearing all of them at once. It also interprets dual staff arrangements as sequential instead of simultaneous. Good job though and thank you for the refund.
I tried it it didn't work .REFUNDED The End
Works great, even when I make my own notations on the sheet music. So, so helpful for figuring out how a section is supposed to sound.
Cannot wait to get my tablet with all my sheet music! Thank you!!

Worked perfectly for me to understand how music sheet is supposed to sound. It does require non-blurry image for full recognition. Also just funny thing - I accidentally caught a piece of my sock on the photo and oh well, turns out my socks can compose music
Was not able to read sheet music on white well lit paper from phone camera. Phone is current technology. Refund requested.
Absolutely amazing accuracy and functionality in an easy-to-use app! Well worth the money!

This is such an impressive app. It is so easy to use - I just snapped photos of each music sheet and it quickly converted them itself into digital music that it can play right away without any other editing required. Remarkable! You can even select from many instruments to hear it back in. Worked first time perfectly. I'm 100% satisfied!
User-friendly. Practical. Flexible. Thank you.
Great app for the price. It's almost perfect, unfortunately it doesn't read triplets correctly. Very useful nonetheless!
Very good app. Would like to recommend it. Be sure to study how to properly use it before reviewing.
Tidak dapat membaca repeat sign.

If you are a musician you need this app!!! I dont normally leave reviews, but is such a great app that i had to. This app is so well made and easy to use that the four dollar price tag shouldn't stop anyone from buying this app. I would pay $20 for this app.
Awsome app. Please keep up the good work.

I don't normally leave review but this is excellent quality app. What I have been looking for. Simple to use and I really like that there is an button for playing individual staff separately. All round a great app, looking forward to the future updates.
It reads music sheets like a robot. With it you do not have to learn how read notes. Amazing.
Not perfect but extremely useful piece of software. I was having trouble interpreting some jazz music and this App helped tremendously. Highly recommend.

This is THE BEST APP EVER. I'm extremely happy with all of the features that this app has, also the accuracy is 99%. I'm a music mayor alumni and I'm flabbergasted with Sheet Music Scanner. $3.99 is mORE THAN A FAIR PRICE FOE THIS MIRACLE.
Fantastic, works great, thank you

No doubt a good quality application of its type available on playstore. I appreciate the work and maintaining fine quality, I can feel in every minor options which average applications do not have. One important feature is missing in this app is Loop option in the baar, you can not lock particular piece of music or baar to play it repeatedly. My suggestion to developers to add this feature which is very good and helpful in such application. Thanks.
So long as I set the tempo a little slower, I find it at a 95% accuracy. Great app to review your tunes with. I've become very reliant on this app to help me and it does. Get it now..

Really the best Music Recognition app available! Truly worth it. It's far better than almost all apps, including things like scanscore on PC. This app makes short work of any PDF and most images you give to it. Thank you so much, this is a truly well developed and clever piece of software! However just a few suggestions - 1. Multi Bar rests are not recognised, if that could be changed, that would be amazing. 2. Triplets are not recognised which can mess up where bar lines are positioned.

Good concept, but... The app sometimes misses notes while playing and saving as midi makes the score saved skip those missed notes. You're better off using musescore and creating the score by hand rather than any sheet music scanner.
replyContent: Sorry to read about the issues. The app gets tested a lot with hundreds of scores and is currently used by over 100k users worldwide but it does have some technical limitations like any other optical recognition and requires a good quality photo of a decent print. Also, it supports export to MusicXML which is the format to use with MuseScore.

content: Wow, very impressive app. Love it!
